    <subsection>
        <title>Factoring Trinomials with Common Factor</title>

        <p>In an ealier section, we learned how to factor out the common factor. For example, <m>2x+6=2(x+3)</m>. When we factor any polynomial, as a first step, we should always check whether we can factor out a common factor. Let's look at some examples.</p>

        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>Factor <m>2z^2-6z-80</m>.</p>

                <p>We will first factor out the common factor, <m>2</m>:<me>2z^2-6z-80=2(z^2-3z-40)</me>In an earlier example, we did the factoring <m>y^2-3y-40=(y+5)(y-8)</m>. Using this result, the full solution of factoring <m>2z^2-6z-80</m> is:<md>
                    <mrow>2z^2-6z-80\amp=2(z^2-3z-40)</mrow>
                    <mrow>\amp=2(z+5)(z-8)</mrow>
                </md></p>
            </statement>
        </example>

        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>Factor <m>p^3q^3-3p^2q^2-40pq</m>.</p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>We will first factor out the common factor <m>pq</m>, and then further factor the trinomial:<md>
                    <mrow>p^3q^3-3p^2q^2-40pq\amp=pq(p^2q^2-3pq-40)</mrow>
                    <mrow>\amp=pq(pq+5)(pq-8)</mrow>
                </md></p>
            </solution>
        </example>

        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>Factor <m>2p^3q-6p^2q^2-80pq^3</m>.</p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>We will first factor out the common factor <m>2pq</m>, and then further factor the trinomial:<md>
                    <mrow>2p^3q-6p^2q^2-80pq^3\amp=2pq(p^2-3pq-40q^2)</mrow>
                    <mrow>\amp=2pq(p+5q)(p-8q)</mrow>
                </md></p>
            </solution>
        </example>

        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>Factor <m>-r^2+3r+40</m>.</p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>We will factor out the common factor <m>-1</m> to make the leading coefficient positive, and then factor the trinomial:<md>
                    <mrow>-r^2+3r+40\amp=-(r^2-3r-40)</mrow>
                    <mrow>\amp=-(r+5)(r-8)</mrow>
                </md></p>
            </solution>
        </example>
    </subsection>

